
** Rename

  - Note: renaming of a temporaray file is not possible. It should be
    dropped and created afterwards.

<example>
  SQL> alter database datafile 'abc.dbf' 
  SQL> autextend on next 20 M
  SQL> maxsize 1000M;
</example>

<example>
  SQL> startup mount;
  SQL> alter database rename file <oldfile> to <newfile>;
</example>


- After an 'alter database' the control file needs to be backuped.

<example>
  SQL> alter database backup controlfile to trace;
</example>

<example>
  SQL> alter database rename global_name to abc;
</example>

<example>
  SQL> alter database default temporary tablespece <ts>;
</example>

** Rename Global_Name


  update sys.props$ set value$='<new global name>' 
  where name='GLOBAL_DB_NAME'; 

